_pdbx_entry_details.compound_details         
;CATALYTIC ACTIVITY: 2-ACETYL-1-ALKYL-SN-GLYCERO-3-PHOSPHOCHOLINE +
 THE CATALYTIC ACTIVITY OF THE ENZYME RESIDES IN THE BETA AND
  GAMMA SUBUNITS, WHEREAS THE ALPHA SUBUNIT HAS REGULATORY ACTIVITY.
 SUBUNIT: CYTOSOLIC PAF-AH IB IS FORMED OF THREE SUBUNITS OF 45 KDA
 (ALPHA), 30 KDA (BETA) AND 29 KDA (GAMMA). THE CATALYTIC ACTIVITY
 OF THE ENZYME RESIDES IN THE BETA AND GAMMA SUBUNITS, WHEREAS THE
 ALPHA SUBUNIT HAS REGULATORY ACTIVITY. TRIMER FORMATION IS NOT
 ESSENTIAL FOR THE CATALYTIC ACTIVITY. INTERACTS WITH DYNEIN AND
 DYNACTIN. INTERACTS WITH RSN.
;
